[2026-03-25 10:15]
CATEGORY: RETRIEVAL_BUG
SERVICE: knowledge
TASK: Make LLM answer in the same language as the question was asked.
SYMPTOM: Spanish question received English answer even after adding "answer in the same language"
         to the system prompt and recreating the Vertex AI context cache.
ROOT_CAUSE: Vertex AI's constrained JSON decoding mode (response_mime_type="application/json"
            + response_schema) overrides the language instruction in the system_instruction.
            When generating tokens into a JSON structure, Gemini defaults to English for string
            field values regardless of what the system prompt says. The same instruction in
            free-text mode (no response_schema) works correctly — verified by testing both
            modes locally against the live cache.
PREVENTED_BY: A smoke test that POSTs a Spanish question and asserts the returned `answer`
              field contains at least one Spanish word (e.g. matches
              /\b(el|la|los|las|es|son|en|de|del|que|se|un|una)\b/i).
              This would have caught the regression immediately after cache recreation and
              before the question was put to the user.
SOLUTION: Append the language instruction to the user query at request time:
            query += "\n\nIMPORTANT: Write your answer in the same language as the question above."
          This instruction in the user turn is respected by the constrained decoder.
          System prompt update (create_cache.py) retained for correctness but is insufficient alone.
DEAD_ENDS: Updating system_instruction in create_cache.py + recreating cache: the instruction
           IS stored and IS followed in free-text mode, but is silently ignored by the
           constrained JSON decoder. Constrained decoding is schema-guided, not semantics-guided.

