TASK: poc1 build pipeline design
SYMPTOM: pageindex.py is in poc/poc1_single_doc/build/ — covered by the
         .gitignore rule `build/`. The file is completely invisible to git.
ROOT_CAUSE: The `build/` gitignore rule exists to exclude compiled artefacts.
            It silently excludes any source directory named build/ as well.
PREVENTED_BY: Before placing source files in any directory, check .gitignore
              for name collisions: `git check-ignore -v <path>` is the exact
              command. Add this to the checklist whenever creating a new dir.
SOLUTION: Rename poc/poc1_single_doc/build/ to a non-gitignored name
          (e.g. indexer/). Update the sys.path.insert line in run_eval.py.
