[2026-04-13]
CATEGORY: BUILD_BUG
SERVICE: poc/indexer
TASK: pageindex monolith → package refactor
SYMPTOM: `python3 indexer/pageindex.py build ...` fails with ImportError after converting
         to a package with relative imports. Previously ran as a script; now fails.
ROOT_CAUSE: Relative imports (`from .config import X`) require the file to be loaded
            as part of a package. Direct script execution sets __name__ = "__main__"
            before package context is established.
PREVENTED_BY: When adding relative imports to any Python file, update all call sites
              to use `python3 -m package.module`, not `python3 path/to/module.py`.
              Do this at the same time as the refactor, not after.
SOLUTION: Updated all build commands to `python3 -m indexer.pageindex build ...`
DEAD_ENDS: None; caught on first test run.

[2026-04-13]
CATEGORY: BUILD_BUG
SERVICE: poc/indexer
TASK: pageindex monolith → package refactor
SYMPTOM: `python3 -m indexer.pageindex` emits RuntimeWarning: "module found in
         sys.modules after import of package, but prior to execution as __main__"
ROOT_CAUSE: __init__.py imported from `pageindex` (re-exporting build_index). When
            Python runs indexer.pageindex as __main__ it imports the package first,
            putting pageindex in sys.modules before it runs as __main__.
PREVENTED_BY: Keep __init__.py shallow — never import from a submodule that may be
              run as __main__. Re-export only from leaf modules (config, llm).
              Consumers of the orchestrator import from indexer.pageindex directly.
SOLUTION: Removed build_index/query_index from __init__.py.
DEAD_ENDS: None; fixed in one pass.

[2026-04-13]
CATEGORY: CONCURRENCY_BUG
SERVICE: poc/indexer
TASK: pageindex hardening for multi-tenant use
SYMPTOM: (latent — not yet triggered) Concurrent build_index calls interleave log
         entries in _BUILD_LOG and mix cost attribution in _BUILD_USAGE.
ROOT_CAUSE: Module-level mutable globals used as per-call state. reset_build_log()
            originally used `= []` (reassignment) — callers that imported the list
            before reset held a stale binding to the old object.
PREVENTED_BY: Never reassign module-level mutable containers in reset functions.
              Use .clear() + .update() to mutate in place. Next: ContextVar migration
              so concurrent calls each get isolated state automatically.
SOLUTION: Changed to _BUILD_LOG.clear() / _BUILD_USAGE.clear(). Full fix (ContextVar)
          deferred to next session.
DEAD_ENDS: None.

